original: Häggstam, Sigfrid Gillis Theodor, kyrkoherde, Tived, f. 18/12/01 i Horn-berga, Skarab. 1., av Alfred H. o. Emma f. Andersson. G. 37 m. Borg-hild Stenström. Barn: Helena f. 39, Kerstin 43, Gunilla 45, Alf 45. — Stud:ex. 25, teol. fik ex. 27, teol. kand. 29, prakt. teol. prov 29, prästex. o. prästv. 30. V. past. i Saleby 30, i Fägre 30-34, kommin. i Kinne-Kleva fr. 35, kyrkoh. i Tived 46. I Kinne-Kleva ordf. i barnav:nd, i skolråd, kassaförv. f. kyrka o. skola, i Tived ordf. i folksk :styr., kyrkostämma o. RKs kretsstyr. m. m. Hobbies: sång o. musik (fiol).
translated: Häggstam, Sigfrid Gillis Theodor was a church pastor in Tived, born on December 18th, 1901 in Hornberga, Skaraborg County, Sweden. He was the first child of Alfred H. and Emma (née Andersson). He got married in 1937 to Borg-hild Stenström and they had four children: Helena (born in 1939), Kerstin (born in 1943), Gunilla (born in 1945), and Alf (also born in 1945). He passed his Studentexamen (university entrance examination) in 1925, theological degree examination in 1927, theological candidate examination in 1929, and practical theological examination in 1929. He passed his priest examination in 1930 and was ordained. He served as a vicar in Saleby in 1930, in Fägre from 1930 to 1934, as a curate in Kinne-Kleva from 1935, and as a church pastor in Tived from 1946. In Kinne-Kleva, he was the chairman of the child welfare committee, school council, treasurer for the church and school. In Tived, he was the chairman of the primary school board, church meeting, and RK district board, among other responsibilities. His hobbies were singing and music (playing violin).
